4:
Hold your formations! Our foes are
not invincible!
6:
They're looking unsteady... But surely
Ciel's soldiers can handle this much—
16:
Yuwel?! You're... alive?
No, you can't handle all three by
yourself—
18:
Do not fret. The Demon Blade herself
is with me.
23:
They didn't put up a fight either. How
disappointing.
26:
The legendary swordsman of House
Tris!
40:
Y-yes, your sister saved me. But
more importantly, do you know
what's going on?
43:
Ciel. The attackers were of the
Farlands.
47:
I concur. Their techniques left no
room for doubt.
52:
I just received a report that the relic
lent to us from Palpebra was stolen...
55:
As well as the research report from
the Voluntas Academy regarding
the Kaleidoscope shifts.
58:
Oh, oh dear... This will be seen as an
act of aggression from the whole of
the Farlands, and not just a
dissenting sect.
59:
If this knowledge is made public, the
past 2 years of cultivating goodwill
will have been for naught! We might
even see a return to the hostilities
displayed 30 years ago!
62:
Then our goal is clear: seize the thief
and reclaim the stolen relic before
anyone else!
68:
You're the fastest. I leave Enlil, and
the fate of our people, in your
hands... Are you willing to bear such
a burden?
72: But of course! I shall not fail you!
76: Leave the rest here to me! Go, Celtie!
81:
I see your sword arm still functions,
Nouin.
85:
Culling foes of this caliber shouldn't
prove to be a challenge, at least.
103:
Have you lost your mind? Always
make sure a foe is defeated before
you turn your back!
109:
I can't find Arum anywhere! I took
my eyes off her for only a moment,
and now she's gone!
113:
First, you need to calm down. Assess
the situation with a level head. Your
sister is strong enough to fend off
these types of foes.
118:
She's just a girl! She's my family, and
it's my duty to protect her!
